# .claude — php-monorepo
#
# Project-level instructions for Claude / AI assistants working in this repo.

## Project overview
PHP monorepo powered by Turborepo.
- `applications/example-app`   — Laravel 13 application
- `modules/example_package`    — Shared PHP library (publishable to Packagist)

## Stack
- PHP 8.3+, Composer 2
- Laravel 13 (applications)
- PHPUnit 12, Laravel Pint, PHPStan 2, Rector 2
- Node.js 20+ / npm 10+ (for Turborepo orchestration only)
- Turborepo 2.x

## Key commands (from repo root)
```bash
npm install          # install JS deps + register git hooks
npm run build        # composer install in all workspaces
npm run test         # PHPUnit across all workspaces
npm run lint         # Pint --test across all workspaces
npm run lint:fix     # Pint (auto-fix) across all workspaces
npm run analyse      # PHPStan across all workspaces
npm run refactor     # Rector dry-run across all workspaces
npm run refactor:fix # Rector apply across all workspaces
```

## Per-workspace commands (from workspace directory)
```bash
composer run test           # run PHPUnit
composer run lint           # pint --test
composer run lint:fix       # pint (auto-fix)
composer run analyse        # phpstan
composer run refactor       # rector --dry-run
composer run refactor:fix   # rector apply
composer run check          # lint + analyse + test in sequence
php artisan serve           # start Laravel dev server
php artisan test            # run Laravel tests
php artisan migrate         # run migrations
php artisan optimize:clear  # clear all caches
```

## PHP code conventions
- Always `declare(strict_types=1)` at the top of every PHP file.
- PSR-12 code style enforced by Laravel Pint.
- PHPStan level 6 — no ignored errors without a comment.
- Full docblocks on all public methods and class properties.
- Constructor property promotion for simple value objects.
- Named arguments for clarity on functions with 3+ parameters.
- No `var_dump()`, `dd()`, or `dump()` in committed code.

## Laravel conventions
- Thin controllers — business logic belongs in Services or Actions.
- Use Form Requests for validation.
- Use Resource classes for API responses.
- Use Jobs for anything that can be queued.
- Use Events + Listeners for side effects.
- Policies for authorization — never inline `Gate::allows()` in controllers.

## Adding a new application
```bash
laravel new applications/my-app --no-interaction
# Add package.json with "name": "@repo/my-app" and turbo tasks
npm install
```

## Adding a new module
Copy `modules/example_package` as a template, update namespace and composer.json name.

## Publishing a module to Packagist
```bash
# 1. Bump version in modules/<name>/composer.json
# 2. Update CHANGELOG.md
git tag example_package-v1.2.3 && git push --tags
# cd_publish.yml workflow handles the rest
```

## Git conventions
- Conventional Commits: `feat(scope): description`
- Never commit directly to `main`.
- Module release tag: `<module_name>-v<semver>`
- App release tag: `v<semver>`

## What NOT to do
- Do not commit `.env` files — ever.
- Do not commit `vendor/` directories.
- Do not use `@phpstan-ignore` without a comment explaining why.
- Do not add `laravel/horizon` or `laravel/sanctum` without configuring them.
